<item>
            <title>[LU-16303] Check message deadline before posting send</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16303</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The LNet message deadline is set when a message is committed for sending. A message can be queued while waiting for send credit(s) after it has been committed. Thus, it is possible for a message deadline to be exceeded while on the queue. We should check for this when posting messages to LND layer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
